<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Thai Party Delegation </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Friendly Talk' With KSDP Chairman </H4>
<F P=102> SK1702061694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0438 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1702061694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- The Chairman of the 
Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party [KSDP], 
Kim Pyong-sik, met and had a friendly talk with the visiting 
delegation of the Social Action Party of Thailand led by its 
Deputy Leader Bunphan Kaeowatthana at the Mansudae Assembly Hall 
Wednesday. 
  The head of the delegation told him that his delegation has 
come to Korea to celebrate the 52nd birthday of the dear leader 
His Excellency Kim Chong-il and hoped that the Korean people 
will make great achievements in accordance with their just idea. 

