<H3> <TI>   Banks Carry Out Arbitration Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1702191694 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1526 GMT 17 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1702191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 17 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
independent newspaper CAPITAL informs that according to Vice 
President of the Mongolbank O. Chuluunbat, the central bank and 
other commercial banks of Mongolia are carrying out dealers 
operations including the arbitration ones at the international 
currency market. But he told nothing neither about the time 
since which such international arbitration operations having 
been stopped by the autumn of 1991 for the reason of the heavy 
losses relating to the hard currency reserves of the country nor 
by whose permission they are being carried out. In the course 
of the first judicial hearing on the sensational case concerning 
the dealers and gold taken place by the end of June to the 
beginning of July 1993 in the city court of the Mongolia capital 
it was announced that the dealers transactions at the 
international market are not still being allowed yet. 

</TEXT>

