<H3> <TI>   Stock Exchange Continues To Sell Securities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1702191494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1529 GMT 17 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1702191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 17 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian Stock Exchange has carried out for the 120th time the 
sale of securities. During the sale there were sold 335,543 
securities of eight joint stock companies. The total turnover 
of the sale amounts for 27.5 million tugrik which is by 13 per 
cent more in reference to their nominal outcome than during the 
previous sale. The maximum rate of securities comes to 171255 
tugrik this time while the lowest one accounts for 1825 tugrik 
each. 
  Next sale of securities at the stock exchange is to be held 
on 24 February. 

</TEXT>

