<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   NCGUB Welcomes Richardson-Suu Kyi Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1702163894 Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma in Burmese 1430 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1702163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the National Coalition Government of </F>
the Union of Burma -- dated 17 February] 
  [Text] The National Coalition Government of the Union of 
Burma, NCGUB, welcomes the meeting between U.S. Congressman Bill 
Richardson and Daw Aung San Suu Kyi. This meeting is one of the 
results of pressures for reform in Burma. The NCGUB also agrees 
with U.S. Congressman Bill Richardson's proposal for a meeting 
between Daw Aung San Suu Kyi and the State Law and Order 
Restoration Council [SLORC]. The NCGUB also firmly believes 
that the political problems in Burma can only be resolved 
through a comprehensive political dialogue and calls on the 
international community to continue pressure on the SLORC until 
this end is achieved. 

