<F P=106> [Report by Liu Zhenyan] </F>
  [Text] Parliament President Marut Bunnak held a luncheon 
for Taiwan President Li Teng-hui at the Central Plaza Hotel 
yesterday. During the luncheon, Li Teng-hui praised Thailand's 
high economic growth. He said that Thailand is admired for 
being able to maintain this despite the stagnation of the global 
economy. Li Teng-hui said that both Taiwan and Thailand 
advocate democracy and freedom. He expressed hope that Taiwan 
and Thailand will enhance cooperation in economy, trade, 
investment, industrial technology, finance, and training on the 
