<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trawlers Warned To Avoid Oil Exploration Site </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1802150794 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 18 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1802150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the agreement reached between the 
Myanmar [Burma] Oil and Gas Enterprise and Texaco Exploration 
Myanmar and Corporation, drilling operations at Ye Mahn Aung-1 
-- a test well in oil exploration block M-13 offshore from 
Tenasserim -- will begin on 14 February. It is estimated that 
drilling operations will last for about 45 days. 
  A mariners' notice has been issued warning fishing trawlers 
to refrain from entering the vicinity of Ye Mahn Aung-1: North 
latitude 13 degrees, 17 minutes, and 41.70 seconds; and East 
longitude 96 degrees, 58 minutes, and 31.40 seconds. 

</TEXT>

